<platform name="c80" cpu="z80">
  <!-- source: MAME ddr/c80.cpp -->
  <!-- year: 1986 -->
  <memory_map>
    <region start="0x00000000" end="0x000007FF" type="rom" name="rom"/>
    <region start="0x00000800" end="0x00000BFF" type="ram" name="ram"/>
  </memory_map>

  <!-- C-80 Trainer (East Germany)
Pasting:
0-F : as is
+ (inc) : ^
- (dec) : V
M : -
GO : X
Test Paste:
-800^11^22^33^44^55^66^77^88^99^-800
Now press up-arrow to confirm the data has been entered.
Commands:
R : REGister
M : MEMory manipulation
G : GO
F10 : RESet
ESC : BRK
Functions (press F1 then the indicated number):
0 : FILL
1 : SAVE
2 : LOAD
3 : LOADP
4 : MOVE
5 : IN
6 : OUT
When REG is chosen, use UP to scroll through the list of regs,
or press 0 thru C to choose one directly:
0 : SP
1 : PC
2 : ... -->
</platform>
